      "text": [
        " خَلُّوا سَبِيلَ الْمُعْسِرِ كَمَا خَلَّاهُ اللَّهُ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Ali Bin Asbaat, from Yaqoub Bin Salim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>: ‘Free the way of the insolvent just as Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Mighty and Majestic Frees it’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "3. A number of our people have narrated from Sahl ibn Ziyad from Ali ibn Asbat from Ya’qub ibn Salim who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that you must leave alone a borrower who has difficulty repaying a loan, just as Allah does (extend the due time for payment of loan if the borrower has difficulty repaying. . . ” (see <a href=\"/#/books/quran:2#h280\"><a href=\"/books/quran:2#h280\">[2:280]</a></a>). "
        ]
      }
